cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper is about semantic segmentation in remote sensing images using deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) with attention-based methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel attention-based framework, which involves the use of multiple attention modules to capture global correlations from different perspectives. This suggests that the paper may also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are related to the development and application of machine learning algorithms. Finally, the paper deals with remote sensing images, which are often analyzed using robotics and automation techniques. Therefore, it may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) category.
